		<description><![CDATA[I hope everyone is enjoying the holidays! Just because we're nearing the end of the year, it doesn't mean you're out of time to bring in new freelance work. Whether you're looking to line-up last minute gigs or trying to schedule January's billable hours, there are plenty of things you can do to market your freelance writing services before year's [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I hope everyone is enjoying the holidays!</p>
<p>Just because we're nearing the end of the year, it doesn't mean you're out of time to bring in new freelance work. Whether you're looking to line-up last minute gigs or trying to schedule January's billable hours, there are plenty of things you can do to market your freelance writing services before year's end.</p>
<p>Here are a few ideas:</p>
<ol>
<li>Email clients you've worked with over the year to thank them for their business. Ask if they have any upcoming projects you can assist with.</li>
<li>When contacting clients, encourage them to order (and pay) quickly to work their next project into the current year's budget. Even clients who usually pay on completion will sometimes pre-pay this time of year so they can deduct the business expense on this year's taxes.</li>
<li>Send a free bonus of some sort to prospects or past clients (like a short report). Not only does it bring their attention to you right now, but it makes you stand out among competing freelancers. Most they work with probably don't do this for them.</li>
<li>Update your rates on your professional website if you've decided to increase (or even decrease) your rates in the New Year.</li>
<li>Release a premium guide or report that promises to help prospects improve their businesses in the New Year. Make sure you close the guide by mentioning your freelance writing services. For example, one of my most successful guides was one on how to write a press release and distribute it online. By teaching prospects some of what you do, you encourage them to try it for themselves. That's when many <em>really </em>start to appreciate the value of hiring a pro.</li>
</ol>
<p>Kick off 2015 already on the minds of your prospects by making the most of the time you have left this year.</p>
<p>Now tell me -- what marketing do <em>you </em>still have planned this year? How do you plan to kick off the New Year?</p>
